@Database CFG_Protocols

@Index HBBS:Docs/Misc/Index.guide/MAIN

@Node Main "Protocols"

  Description:

  The HBBS:System/Protocols file defines the setting for the transfer
  protocols that users are allowed to use.

  There must be one of each option for each protocol you define.

  Options:

  Name_XX=<string>                @{" More... " link Name_XX}
  Type_XX=<string>                @{" More... " link Type_XX}
  ModuleName_XX=<string>          @{" More... " link ModuleName_XX}
  ModuleOpts_XX=<string>          @{" More... " link ModuleOpts_XX}
  AllowDL_XX=<boolean>            @{" More... " link AllowDL_XX}
  AllowDL_XX=<boolean>            @{" More... " link AllowUL_XX}

  Example for ZModem via the XPR door.
  ====================================

  Name_1=Normal ZModem (xprzmodem.library ZModem)
  Type_1=UNIDIRECTIONAL
  ModuleName_1=XPR
  ModuleOpts_1=xprzmodem.library O=TC,OR,B16,F0,E10,AY,DN,KY,SN,RN,P,M1024
  AllowDL_1=ON
  AllowUL_1=ON


@EndNode

@Node Name_XX "Name_XX"

  Name_XX=<string>

    E.G.

    Name_1=ZModem (via xprzmodem.library)

    Default = none, must be specified

    This option sets the display name that the user sees when they're
    selecting a transfer protocol to use.

@EndNode

@Node Type_XX "Type_XX"

  Type_XX=<string>

    E.G.

    Type_1=BIDIRECTIONAL

    This option can only be set to either BIDIRECTIONAL or UNIDIRECTIONAL.

    It specifies the type of transfer.

@EndNode

@Node ModuleName_XX "ModuleName_XX"

  ModuleName_XX=<string>

    E.G.

    ModuleName_1=XPR

    This option specifies the module (in fact, a system door) to be
    used, the a system door with the same name must be defined!

@EndNode

@Node ModuleOpts_XX "ModuleOpts_XX"

  ModuleOpts_XX=<string>

    E.G.

    ModuleOpts_1=xprzmodem.library O=TC,OR,B16,F0,E10,AY,DN,KY,SN,RN,P,M1024

    This lets you specify what options to use for the module (system door)
    you want to use.  In the case of the XPR door it lets you specify
    which xpr library to use and the xpr libraries options.

@EndNode

@Node AllowUL_XX "AllowUL_XX"

  AllowUL_XX=<boolean>

    E.G.

    AllowUL_1=YES

    This lets you specify if a protocol can be used from the UPLOAD door.

@EndNode


@Node AllowDL_XX "AllowDL_XX"

  AllowDL_XX=<boolean>

    E.G.

    AllowDL_1=YES

    This lets you specify if a protocol can be used from the DOWNLOAD door.

@EndNode


